  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nI am trying to sync my node but it takes too much time.\r\nI am just wondering if the problem is not due to my disk who is HDD and not SSD.\r\nFor example on my syncing, I can see that the current block is just at 60 ebfore the highest one but it looks like new blocks come faster than the time my server take to import old one.\r\n\r\nMy server is Intel Xeon D1520 - 4c/8t - 2.2 GHz/2.6 GHz, 32 Go ECC 2133 MHz and 2 TB drive and 250mbps bandwidth.\r\n\r\nThere is an example of result of the syncing rpc endpoint : \r\n```\r\n{\r\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n    \"id\": 1,\r\n    \"result\": {\r\n        \"currentBlock\": \"0x11dfc15\",\r\n        \"healedBytecodeBytes\": \"0x73eb173\",\r\n        \"healedBytecodes\": \"0x3fb9\",\r\n        \"healedTrienodeBytes\": \"0x6182ed433\",\r\n        \"healedTrienodes\": \"0x47fcdb4\",\r\n        \"healingBytecode\": \"0x0\",\r\n        \"healingTrienodes\": \"0x454\",\r\n        \"highestBlock\": \"0x11dfc5a\",\r\n        \"startingBlock\": \"0x11df124\",\r\n        \"syncedAccountBytes\": \"0xcffc64156\",\r\n        \"syncedAccounts\": \"0x1115baac\",\r\n        \"syncedBytecodeBytes\": \"0x1c3607e8b\",\r\n        \"syncedBytecodes\": \"0x10a260\",\r\n        \"syncedStorage\": \"0x43f6267e\",\r\n        \"syncedStorageBytes\": \"0x3922c34475\"\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nSomeone of you already got this issue or do you think it will be sync at one moment ?",
